---
import "../../styles/global.css";
import "../../styles/cocometric.css";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <meta name="theme-color" content="#01050a" />
  <meta name="description" content="Cocometric designs, builds, and supports private local infrastructure for storage, AI, networking, security, and internal tools." />
  <title>Cocometric — Private local infrastructure</title>
</head>
<body>
  <a class="skip-link" href="#contact">Skip to contact</a>

  <div class="loading" id="loading" role="status" aria-live="polite">
    <div class="loading-inner">
      <p class="loading-copy" id="loading-copy">Loading Cocometric hardware</p>
      <div class="loading-track" aria-hidden="true"><div class="loading-bar" id="loading-bar"></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <header class="header">
    <a class="brand" href="/cocometric/" aria-label="Cocometric home">
      <span class="mark" aria-hidden="true"><i></i></span>
      <span>Cocometric</span>
    </a>
    <a class="header-cta" href="#contact">Contact for services</a>
  </header>

  <div class="scene" id="scene" aria-hidden="true">
    <canvas id="server-canvas"></canvas>
    <div class="vignette"></div>
  </div>

  <section class="copy" id="copy" aria-live="polite">
    <p class="step" id="stage-step">Cocometric system · 01</p>
    <h1 id="stage-title">One system. Every layer visible.</h1>
    <p class="copy-note" id="stage-note">Scroll through the actual server model to inspect the rack, storage, compute, accelerators, cooling, power, and network hardware.</p>
    <div class="component-tags" id="stage-tags" aria-hidden="true">
      <span>Rack</span><span>Storage</span><span>Compute</span><span>GPU</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <nav class="stage-nav" aria-label="3D server components">
    <button type="button" class="is-active" data-stage-button="0" aria-label="Show complete system">01</button>
    <button type="button" data-stage-button="1" aria-label="Show rack and chassis">02</button>
    <button type="button" data-stage-button="2" aria-label="Show storage drives">03</button>
    <button type="button" data-stage-button="3" aria-label="Show motherboard, CPU, and memory">04</button>
    <button type="button" data-stage-button="4" aria-label="Show GPU accelerators">05</button>
    <button type="button" data-stage-button="5" aria-label="Show cooling system">06</button>
    <button type="button" data-stage-button="6" aria-label="Show power and networking">07</button>
  </nav>

  <div class="scroll-cue" id="scroll-cue">Scroll to inspect</div>

  <main class="track" id="track">
    <section class="beat" data-stage="0"><div class="sr-only"><h2>Complete Cocometric system</h2><p>Full exploded view of the real three-dimensional server model.</p></div></section>
    <section class="beat" data-stage="1"><div class="sr-only"><h2>Rack and chassis</h2><p>Serviceable rack enclosure, rails, chassis, and installed server bays.</p></div></section>
    <section class="beat" data-stage="2"><div class="sr-only"><h2>Storage</h2><p>Six removable drives for primary data, snapshots, and backup tiers.</p></div></section>
    <section class="beat" data-stage="3"><div class="sr-only"><h2>Compute</h2><p>Motherboard, dual processors, heat sinks, and twelve memory modules.</p></div></section>
    <section class="beat" data-stage="4"><div class="sr-only"><h2>AI accelerators</h2><p>Two GPU assemblies for local model inference and accelerated workloads.</p></div></section>
    <section class="beat" data-stage="5"><div class="sr-only"><h2>Cooling</h2><p>Six fan assemblies and a dedicated fan wall for controlled airflow.</p></div></section>
    <section class="beat" data-stage="6"><div class="sr-only"><h2>Power and network</h2><p>Redundant power supplies and a dedicated multi-port network interface.</p></div></section>

    <section class="final" id="contact">
      <div class="final-card">
        <p class="step">Cocometric services</p>
        <h2>Own the hardware, or run it as a managed system.</h2>
        <p>Purpose-built local infrastructure for private AI, storage, video, networking, and internal tools. Each system is configured, documented, tested, and handed off with a clear support path.</p>
        <div class="service-options">
          <div class="service-option"><strong>Build and own it</strong><span>Hardware selection, assembly, deployment, migration, documentation, and handoff.</span></div>
          <div class="service-option"><strong>Managed operation</strong><span>Ongoing monitoring, upgrades, backups, recovery testing, and support.</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="actions">
          <a class="button button-primary" href="/contact/?topic=cocometric-services">Scope a system</a>
          <a class="button button-secondary" href="#track">Inspect it again</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <noscript><p style="position:fixed;z-index:50;left:20px;bottom:20px;max-width:42ch;color:#eef3f7">JavaScript is required for the interactive server model. The service details and contact section remain available below.</p></noscript>

  <script src="../../scripts/cocometric-viewer.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
